Pre-Game Insights: The fourth edition of the UEFA Nations League gets underway this week, where the Faroe Islands and North Macedonia will hope to gain promotion from League C.
North Macedonia hopes to repeat their previous friendly victory against Faroe Islands, with Bojan Miovski scoring the only goal.
Each of the other two countries in their pool – Armenia and Latvia – are newcomers to League C after being relegated from League B and promoted from League D, respectively, last year.
